Ventured out for the first time for food-pickup in a LONG time because I've been staying home and ordering contactless delivery because of COVID. Came here to grab a chicken burrito for lunch, which was hot and delicious and exactly what I was craving.  While I was waiting for my pickup order, I witnessed a super rude woman at the counter yelling about onions being in her food. 🤦‍♀️Come on, people. Have some humanity.  1) this is a mexican place. there's basically onions, tomatoes, and peppers brasied into everything. That's what makes it mexican food. 2) Don't be rude to staff. Even if you said 'no onion' when you ordered. (This woman admitted that she *didn't* say no onions...🤦‍♀️) These are hard-working staff at a small local-owned food stand just trying to do their jobs during an insane and stressful time to be a food-service worker. Just ask for something else instead, ask for your money back if you can't eat anything, or realize you messed up and shouldn't have ordered what you did and pick out the onions and move on with your day. Ugh. 3) I went back and threw a 100% tip in the jar and apologized on behalf of the other customer to the worker bearing the brunt of her wrath.  So dumb to even have to write this. But the staff seemed worried about the wrath of the other person (who was threatening to have her 'powerful local friends' post all over social media about these dredded onions...) so I wanted to counter that, for humanity's sake.  Anyways, if you're looking for hot and affordable tacos and burritos with a ton of veggies in them and lots of upgrade options, this is your place! (Get a side of the home-made salsa for dipping - yum!)

I'll be one of the people to add to the horrible ratings. Only reason why this place has business still is because of its location in close proximity to bars. It's 5/4 (derby day), 11:00 pm and I just got out of work, I'm a bartender at a nearby bar. The run a special that says dinners for $6 on Friday and Saturdays. Multiple times I have come after brunch and dinner service when I'm done with work (we're open till 10). Always have I been served the special for $6. I have a set schedule with demands I work those days of the week. Quite frankly the only reason why I go to this place at all is for the special because it's so cheap. The food is barely edible, but again, hey it's cheap. I come in tonight and order the steak taco dinner and they try to charge me almost $12. I ask them about the special. The counter girl looked caught and turned to one of the line cooks and asked him about it. He looked at me and said no. I told her by law if you have a special in a place that serves food you have to have that special all day. It was only $11 (I work in a restaurant full service and fast casual so I know). He didn't care turned back around. Then she asked someone else and he said no. She said he said the special was only between certain times. I said that is not true, for the 6 months I've worked around the corner that's never been the case. She said I could talked to him myself (she was rude and clearly disinterested). I went over to talk to the man cooking and after him ignoring me for a bit, he had an immature attitude (He had to be over 45 at least) and said the law I pointed out wasn't true, they can Do what they want. I asked him well what imaginary time brackets do you guys do the special then. He blurted our 11am-9pm. Again, that's a crock of baloney because I've always gotten food from there after work and we close at 10 and I don't get out until even later. The money isn't the issue (I have enough of that) it's the principle. They are dishonest to their guests and price gouging. Not to mention trying to take advantage of patrons potentially intoxicated and leaving the nearby bars. It's illegal (the law I mentioned exists) and unethical. Especially for their barely edible food. Also, half the time I'm in there you'll be standing at the counter and it can be empty in that tiny place and they won't even acknowledge you when you're standing right in front of them. Very rude. I'm going to go to big wig right across the street from my high rise and get better food and quality service. Never coming back and I don't suggest you do either the food is nasty, hence all the cheap specials.

Maybe its because I am Mexican and therefore am not easily impressed by tacos, but they are for sure not worth the price tag and the menu is rather small.
Solid burritos for a good price. A great option if you're bar-hopping and just want a quick, inexpensive bite.

Flash's major downside is that it's cash only, but there is a bank right across the street so I guess if you are willing to plan ahead you shall be rewarded. With tacos. And burritos. Most expensive and classier taco places may exist within the same block but Flash is always just what I need. Great taste goes to amazing after a few drinks and it's right up under the train so it's good for the commuter too.
This place has a great location. The tacos do takes more time than I sometimes expect. The taste is consistent and it fills me up on those really hungry late nights.

All of my experiences at Flash Taco have been after hours and after drinking lol.  So you may want to take my review with a grain of salt.  But Flash Taco is really good after a long night.  Weekends you can expect a little bit of a line.  But it moves fast.  It's the closest to street food you are going to get on that corner of Chicago.  Burritos could be a little bit bigger for the price (8 dollars) but you are pretty much just there to sober up.  The one thing I like is the hot spicy sauce.  But beware it is extremely spicy.
Too many people for only 2 employees working at the time, so took a while. But worth it. DELICIOUS! !! I was also drnk, so thats a factor.
I saw a roach, that is enough said about this location.
FLASH TACOS HAS DAILY SPECIALS THAT ARE AFFORDABLE EVEN TO ME-A LOW FIXED-INCOME INDIVIDUAL ! THE WEDNESDAY $4 CHICKEN BURRITOS VERY TASTY & FRESH ! A MUST TRY
super spicy sauce! delicious! great late night!
Please, just don't go. I went through it so you wouldn't have to.  If your friend says, "it was really good," then it was 2:00AM, & they were really drunk.
terrrible food
Great place for greasy food when it's 1am in the morning.  I needed them to correct an order and they were happy to do so.
best tacos around. Definatly get the steak tacos.

What can I say for taco's this place is to die for. Although don't forgert cash because they DO NOT take cards. Thier torta's are delicious and all of the cooks and staff are very friendly, fast and warm towards the cutomers. Every time Ive come I have never been disapointed with the service. Only dispointed if I forgot to bring cash, which has happened a few times.

The tortas here are great, and the quality of the meat is pretty darn good. The locals all come here, and I trust their judgement. The only thing I would count against Flash is the fact their quality suffers a bit on busy late nights, and I've gotten the wrong order twice, but since its so good, I'll deal with it!
Flash taco provides quality tacos without the lines of Big star. The new design is a questionable decision. Service is usually quality, but on one ocassion my pork quesadilla included uncooked pork.

great fast food!

Great food! Never fail.  Great open air feel, but it is a little cramped. This time they were doing some renovations, so three angel of paint want great, but the torta cubana wad very good!
Great during the summer time and for the latenight hangover! super busy during the weekend in nice weather. try it on a Wednesday.

You should only eat here if you've had too much to drink. Who would consider trusting  a place that claims to feature hot dogs, tacos, and pizza? Expect greasy awfulness that might actually be worse than taco bell I've gotten sick, but I'm not sure if that was the tacos or the alcohol. There are plenty of better late night options in this area now, so avoid at all costs. Long lines and lousy food.

You know, if you have to, you have to. This should be a last resort. I understand maybe 15 years ago when there weren't many other options for late night drunken sustenance, but let's be clear - this isn't good food. Sure, it'll do in a pinch and it may taste good at the time (and if the time isn't 5am, what are you doing here?), but you'll regret it. Hey, if you're eating here I'm sure it's not because you sought out a review on google + and decided it was a destination you couldn't miss, so go for it.

Where you go if you're in wicker park after a night out...  you'll find lots of people here late night on the weekends.  The music is a little too loud, in my opinion.  Its ok for a spot to get some food in you after a night of drinking...
The only reason this place gets business is because it's open late night. The food, is just bad.
It's ok is the perfect way to sum up your trip to Flash Taco. Yes it's open late & they crank em out but it's nothing really to write home about.
